<taxonomicNameLabel box="[673,802,1974,1999]" pageId="3" pageNumber="543">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in general appearance, but differing from it as follows: Male 
<number box="[215,228,2010,2035]" pageId="3" pageNumber="543" value="5.0">5</number>
th abdominal sternite (
<figureCitation box="[481,608,2010,2035]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1908,1931]" captionTargetBox="[203,1348,208,1868]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[192,1394,175,1903]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 18. Male 5 th sternite and terminalia of Cephalispa triquetra sp. nov.: 13. Male 5 th sternite in ventral view (setae omitted on the left side). 14. Same in lateral view (setae omitted). 15. Epandrium, surstylus and cerci in lateral view. 16. Same in dorsal view (setae omitted on the left side). 17. Hypandrium, postgonite and phallus in lateral view. 18. Distiphallus in dorsal view. (Scale bars = 0.2 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262978/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="543">
Figs 
<number box="[537,608,2011,2035]" pageId="3" pageNumber="543" value="13.5" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="13.0">13‒14</number>
</figureCitation>
) nearly straight apically in lateral view.
</paragraph>
