<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="546" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,709]" pageId="6" pageNumber="546">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,613,638]" pageId="6" pageNumber="546">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Cui &amp; Xue, 1995" authorityName="Cui &amp; Xue" authorityYear="1995" box="[601,896,613,638]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Cephalispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fani">
<emphasis box="[601,681,613,637]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="546">C. fani</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Cui" box="[692,896,613,638]" pageId="6" pageNumber="546" refString="Cui, Y., Xue, W. &amp; Chen, C. (1995) A study of the genus Cephalispa Malloch of China (Diptera: Muscidae). Entomologia Sinica, 2, 18 - 34. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1744 - 7917.1995. tb 00019. x" type="journal article" year="1995">
Cui &amp; Xue, 
<number box="[840,896,613,638]" pageId="6" pageNumber="546" value="1995.0">1995</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[972,1042,613,638]" name="China" pageId="6" pageNumber="546">China</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1057,1244,613,638]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Cephalispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="okinawaensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1057,1244,613,638]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="546">C. okinawaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1255,1348,613,638]" pageId="6" pageNumber="546">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1255,1348,613,638]" pageId="6" pageNumber="546" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Shinonaga" authorityName="Shinonaga" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Lispocephala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xanthogaster" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="546">C. xanthogaster</emphasis>
(Shinonaga)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[447,575,648,673]" pageId="6" pageNumber="546">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[447,575,648,673]" pageId="6" pageNumber="546">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
It is distinguishable from them by the strongly curved postgonite and phallus (
<figureCitation box="[159,243,684,709]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1908,1931]" captionTargetBox="[203,1348,208,1868]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[192,1394,175,1903]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 18. Male 5 th sternite and terminalia of Cephalispa triquetra sp. nov.: 13. Male 5 th sternite in ventral view (setae omitted on the left side). 14. Same in lateral view (setae omitted). 15. Epandrium, surstylus and cerci in lateral view. 16. Same in dorsal view (setae omitted on the left side). 17. Hypandrium, postgonite and phallus in lateral view. 18. Distiphallus in dorsal view. (Scale bars = 0.2 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262978/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="546">
Fig. 
<number box="[212,243,684,708]" pageId="6" pageNumber="546" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
